Class BaseFeedApiKeyConnector

java.lang.Object
grafioschtrader.connector.instrument.BaseFeedConnector
grafioschtrader.connector.instrument.BaseFeedApiKeyConnector
All Implemented Interfaces:
IFeedConnector
Direct Known Subclasses:
AlphaVantageFeedConnector, CryptoCompareFeedConnector, EodHistoricalDataConnector, FinnhubConnector, StockDataFeedConnector, TwelvedataFeedConnector
public abstract class BaseFeedApiKeyConnector extends BaseFeedConnector
Abstract base class for feed connectors that require API key authentication and subscription management. This class extends BaseFeedConnector to add secure API key handling, subscription validation, and enhanced error reporting that protects sensitive authentication information.

Subscription Management

Many data providers offer different subscription tiers with varying capabilities. This class provides infrastructure to:

  • Validate that the current subscription supports requested data types
  • Manage subscription type information
  • Provide extension points for subscription-specific validation

Security Features

The class implements several security measures:

  • API Key Hiding: Automatically removes API keys from URLs in error messages
  • Parameter Replacement: Replaces API key parameters with placeholder text
  • URL Sanitization: Removes query parameters that might contain sensitive data

Implementation Guidelines

Subclasses should:

  • Override hasAPISubscriptionSupport() to implement subscription validation
  • Use getApiKey() to access the API key for requests
  • Use standardApiKeyReplacementForErrors() for consistent error message sanitization
  • Call resetConnectorApiKey() when API key configuration changes

    • standardApiKeyReplacementForErrors

      protected String standardApiKeyReplacementForErrors(String url, String tokenParamName)
      Sanitizes URLs by replacing API key parameters with placeholder text for error reporting. This method uses regular expressions to find and replace API key values in URLs while preserving the URL structure for debugging purposes.
      Parameters:
      url - the URL that may contain an API key parameter
      tokenParamName - the name of the parameter that contains the API key (e.g., "apikey", "token")
      Returns:
      the sanitized URL with the API key value replaced by ERROR_API_KEY_REPLACEMENT

    • hideApiKeyForError

      public String hideApiKeyForError(String url)
      Hides API keys and other sensitive query parameters from URLs in error messages. This method removes all query parameters from URLs to prevent accidental exposure of authentication information in logs and error reports. This is a more aggressive approach than parameter-specific replacement.
      Overrides:
      hideApiKeyForError in class BaseFeedConnector
      Parameters:
      url - the URL that may contain sensitive query parameters
      Returns:
      the URL with all query parameters removed (everything after the first '?')

    • resetConnectorApiKey

      public void resetConnectorApiKey()
      Clears the cached API key, forcing it to be reloaded from the database on next access. This method should be called when API key configuration changes or when the connector needs to refresh its authentication credentials.

      Common scenarios for calling this method:

      • After updating API key configuration in the admin interface
      • When authentication errors suggest the cached key may be stale
      • During connector reconfiguration or testing
